# Commenting And Maintainability Standard

All production code changes must include maintainability-oriented comments.

- Document intent and reasoning, not obvious syntax.
- Add comments for:
  - Non-trivial business rules, data transforms, and fallback logic
  - Async flows, side effects, cleanup, and state transitions
  - Cross-system mappings (UI <-> API <-> persistence contracts)
  - Temporary constraints and known follow-up work
- Keep comments close to the code they explain.
- Update comments whenever behavior changes.
- Do not leave undocumented complex logic.

## Examples

```ts
// Normalize partner identity with safe fallbacks so referrals remain actionable.
const partnerName = input.partnerName.trim() || account.organization || 'community partner'

// Revoke object URLs on unmount to avoid leaking browser memory.
return () => URL.revokeObjectURL(previewUrl)
```
